      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "### \u2139\ufe0f About This Report\nAuthorization approvals, declines, and reversals from the FIS STDAUTH Data XTRACT feed (v2.7). Sourced from **`reporting.fact_authorization`** and pre-aggregated view **`reporting.vw_auth_decline_summary`**.\n\n| Column | Source | Meaning |\n|--------|--------|--------|\n| Response Code | `fact_authorization.response_code` | FIS auth response: 0=Approved, 51=Insufficient funds, 57=Not permitted, etc. |\n| Response Description | `fact_authorization.response_description` | Human-readable response text |\n| Is Reversed | `fact_authorization.is_reversed` | True if auth was subsequently reversed |\n| Auth Amount | `fact_authorization.authorization_amount` | Requested authorization amount in card currency |\n| Settle Balance | `fact_authorization.settle_balance` | Purse balance after settlement |\n| Purse Name | `fact_authorization.purse_name` | Which purse was charged (OTC2100, FOD2100, CMB2100) |\n| MCC | `fact_authorization.mcc` | Merchant Category Code |\n| Merchant Name | `fact_authorization.merchant_name` | Where the card was used |\n\n> \u26a0\ufe0f **This report requires FIS STDAUTH XTRACT feeds to be active.** Pending DM-03 confirmation from Kendra Williams. Data will populate automatically when FIS begins delivering daily STDAUTH files to the XTRACT SFTP endpoint.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "10.4.3",
      "title": "",
      "type": "text"
    },
